<h1>Alison Hawke</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://quantumtea.com/now/">quantumtea.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
St Louis
MO
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Director of Quality Advocacy, Asynchrony Labs
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I lead a team of first class software QAs helping get awesome software delivered to clients
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I'm training my team to be better QAs than me. I craft (knit, spin yarn) to get out of my head, and I learn Chinese Kenpo karate for fun.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
My job is to clear obstacles and train people, but to do that I need time to sit and think about how to solve the hard problems. This idea time is never wasted.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
"The Accidental Creative" by Todd Henry
</p>

